  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Wireshark — Simulating Phishing Attacks with the HTTP Protocol Tree$escape$,
  $escape$To simulate phishing attacks using Wireshark, filter the HTTP protocol tree for packets containing suspicious URL patterns. Use the 'http.request_uri' field to identify potentially malicious URLs. You can also use the 'http.host' field to filter by domain name. For example, `http.request_uri =~ 'https://example.com/login'` will display all HTTP packets containing the URL 'https://example.com/login'.$escape$,
  $escape$tshark -r capture.pcap -Y 'http.request_uri =~ "https://example\.com/login"'$escape$,
